snippet: David Phelps, who was no higher than eighth on the depth chart of starting pitchers in spring training, was impressive in beating the Red Sox.
abstract: Tyler Kepner On Baseball column notes that New York Yankees pitcher David Phelps, who was no higher than eighth on the depth chart of starting pitchers in spring training, was impressive in his latest outing against the Boston Red Sox.
lead_paragraph: David Phelps, who was no higher than eighth on the depth chart of starting pitchers in spring training, was impressive in beating the Red Sox.
